                     <interp inst="def1-2051-18380820" type="surname" value="EBBS"></interp>
                     <interp inst="def1-2051-18380820" type="given" value="JOHN"></interp>
                     <hi rend="largeCaps">JOHN EBBS</hi>
                  </persName> was indicted<rs id="t18380820-2051-offence-1" type="offenceDescription">
                     <interp inst="t18380820-2051-offence-1" type="offenceCategory" value="theft"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18380820-2051-offence-1" type="offenceSubcategory" value="simpleLarceny"></interp> for stealing, on the <rs id="t18380820-cd-256" type="crimeDate">
                        <join result="offenceCrimeDate" targOrder="Y" targets="t18380820-2051-offence-1 t18380820-cd-256"></join>7th of August</rs>, 12 keys, value 2<hi rend="italic">s</hi>. 6<hi rend="italic">d</hi>.; 1 bag, value 1<hi rend="italic">s</hi>. 4<hi rend="italic">d</hi>.; 8 sovereigns, 8 half—sove<lb></lb>reigns, 21 half-crowns, 37 shillings, 1 sixpence, 2 pence, and 8 halfpence; the goods and monies of <persName id="t18380820-name-1534" type="victimName">
                        <interp inst="t18380820-name-1534" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18380820-name-1534" type="surname" value="SHEPHERD"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18380820-name-1534" type="given" value="JOHN ANTHONY"></interp>
                        <join result="offenceVictim" targOrder="Y" targets="t18380820-2051-offence-1 t18380820-name-1534"></join>John Anthony Shepherd</persName>.</rs>
               </p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18380820-name-1535" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18380820-name-1535" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18380820-name-1535" type="surname" value="SHEPHERD"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18380820-name-1535" type="given" value="JOHN ANTHONY"></interp>JOHN ANTHONY SHEPHERD</persName>
                  </hi>. I am an undertaker, and live in London-street,</p>
               <xptr type="pageFacsimile" doc="183808200231"></xptr>
               <p>Greenwich. On the 7th of August I was at Lee races with my wife and family, in an open landau—my wife had a bag—I know it con<lb></lb>tained some money, but I do not know what—I can only swear to one bit of paper that was in it—this bag, keys, and paper are mine—(<hi rend="italic">looking at them</hi>)—they were taken out of the carriage—Mrs. Shepherd had got them—she is lame, and not able to attend here-when she got up she left this bag on the seat—the paper is an agreement of Mr. Farmer's.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="italic">Cross-examined by</hi> 
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">MR. PHILLIPS</hi>. <hi rend="italic">Q.</hi> Did you see the keys put into the bag? <hi rend="italic">A.</hi> No; I only know they are mine.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18380820-name-1536" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18380820-name-1536" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18380820-name-1536" type="surname" value="SHEPPARD"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18380820-name-1536" type="given" value="DAVID"></interp>DAVID SHEPPARD</persName>
                  </hi>. I was a police-constable. On the 7th of August, I was at the races, and the prisoner was given into my custody—I found the bag in Mr. Shepherd's possession—I took it from him—it contained the money stated.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18380820-name-1537" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18380820-name-1537" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18380820-name-1537" type="surname" value="WALLIS"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18380820-name-1537" type="given" value="JOHN WILLIAM"></interp>JOHN WILLIAM WALLIS</persName>
                  </hi>. I was at the races—I saw the prosecutor and his wife in the carriage—I saw the prisoner get up behind, on the hind wheel of the carriage, and take a black silk bag—I have no question that that is the bag—(<hi rend="italic">looking at it</hi>)—he jumped down, and fan away—I ran after him—he threw the bag away—I took him and held him—I saw the keys and money taken from the bag—there was gold and silver.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="italic">Cross-examined. Q.</hi> Are you certain of the prisoner? <hi rend="italic">A.</hi> I have no doubt of it—there were many persons there—I had not seen the prisoner before.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">COURT</hi>. <hi rend="italic">Q.</hi> From the time of his taking the bag and your taking him, and his dropping it, had you lost sight of him? <hi rend="italic">A.</hi> No.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18380820-name-1538" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18380820-name-1538" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18380820-name-1538" type="surname" value="SEARLES"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18380820-name-1538" type="given" value="WILLIAM"></interp>WILLIAM SEARLES</persName>
                  </hi>. I was at the races—I picked up the bag and deli<lb></lb>vered it to the prosecutor—I did not see who dropped it.</p>
               <p>(The prisoner received a good character.)</p>
               <p>
